      "writtenOn": "2021-03-16T22:35:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Good point. Actually, that wasn\u0027t a conscious decision.\n\nThat being said, I still want to ship the current implementation. Because\n1. If an user is interested in a step in one builder, it\u0027s likely they will also be interested in the step with the same name in another builder.\nFor instance, in the bugs linked in the CL. Users want to pin \"lookup GN args\" and \"gs_util repo_state\". If those steps are in other builders as well, they are likely to be interested in them too.\n\n2. The implementation is simpler than supporting builder/project scoped configuration. We can always change it to a builder/project scoped configuration later if there are user requests for it.",
